HEADWORD: Obstriction
<hw>Ob*stric"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>obstringere</ets>, <ets>obstrictum</ets>, to bind to or
about.]</ety> <def>The state of being constrained, bound, or obliged;
that which constrains or obliges; obligation; bond.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

